SIMPLE: overturn
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Overturn
<hw>O`ver*turn"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Overturned</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Overturning</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To turn
or throw from a basis, foundation, or position; to overset; <as>as, to
<ex>overturn</ex> a carriage or a building</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To subvert; to destroy; to overthrow.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To overpower; to conquer.</def>
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To demolish; overthrow. See
<er>Demolish</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overturn</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Overturn
<hw>O"ver*turn`</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act off overturning, or the
state of being overturned or subverted; overthrow; <as>as, an
<ex>overturn</ex> of parties</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overturnable</ent>⟦br⟧
